text:

name: CNN
text:
Dr. Anthony Fauci did not consent to being featured in a new advertisement from the Trump campaign touting President Trump's handling of the pandemic. 

Instead, the nation's leading infectious disease expert told CNN his words were taken out of context. https://t.co/bLobzuxvIE

name: CNN
text: "The comments attributed to me without my permission... were taken out of context from a broad statement I made months ago about the efforts of federal public health officials," Fauci said in a statement provided exclusively to CNN https://t.co/6Wi6sJ28yb

name: CNN
text: Bhagavan "Doc" Antle, one of the many characters in Netflix's "Tiger King," has been indicted on wildlife trafficking charges after an investigation by Virginia Attorney General Mark Herring. https://t.co/GPhviPQbvC

text: Twitter added a warning label to a tweet from President Donald Trump that claimed, without evidence, he is immune to coronavirus after his physician cleared him to resume public activities. https://t.co/rsIqJ0ABFU

text: President Donald Trump's reelection campaign on Sunday revived its push for an in-person presidential debate even though it seems the Joe Biden campaign -- and the debate commission -- have moved on. https://t.co/ghuofPwV3x

name: CNN
text:
Rafael Nadal beats Novak Djokovic in the French Open final to win the competition for the 13th time.

It also moves Nadal to 20 grand slam wins -- tying with Roger Federer's men's all-time record. https://t.co/8kQaTAfHxB

name: CNN
text: More than half of US states are seeing an increase in new Covid-19 cases, with five states -- Montana, New Mexico, North Carolina, Tennessee and Vermont -- reporting a jump of more than 50% in one week. https://t.co/mRwUbX3eN0
